unique_values: Click each square to toggle whether the LED for that position should be lit. Then click the [i]Update LED[/i] button to set the LED display on the micro:bit.
Move the sliders to adjust the parameters of the "Adjust HSL" effect on the sprite using JavaScript code.
Try toggling layer visibility in the layers bar.  A black layer with white spot lights using 'destination out' creates the lighting effect.

Use the arrow keys to move and click or touch to create an explosion. Listen carefully as you move around the layout - every sound is positioned, and the volume/pan is adjusted depending on the source.

- Drag and Drop pieces using touch controls or mouse

- When the promotion screen appears, tap the desired piece

- If you feel like restarting the game, tap the circular arrow button
Click or touch to run a water transition.

You can also change the firework color by adjusting the RGB sliders.

Put the meat patty on the grill and let it cook. Pay attention to your patty appearance:
[size=96][icon=Patty0][icon=Patty1][icon=Patty2][icon=Patty3][/size]

1st and 2nd are undercooked. 3rd is perfect. 4th is overcooked and will adhere to the grill.

Reach the arrows marking the current objective as quickly as possible. Right now, hitting cones or running over the grass/red sand fails the test.

[color=#FFD700]Gold time: 35s[/color]   |   [color=#B0B0B0]Silver time: 45s[/color]   |   [color=#CD853F]Bronze time: 60s[/color]

Controls:
\[Arrows] to move the car

Press \[Space] to start...
Use the arrow keys to move around and press the spacebar to jump.

Controls:

[color=#ffff00]Left click:[/color] pick/place objects (hold [color=#ffff00]Ctrl[/color] to place many)
[color=#ffff00]Right click:[/color] rotate picked object
[color=#ffff00]Scroll:[/color] rotate/zoom, depending on the camera angle
[color=#ffff00]Space:[/color] change camera angle

- Move object outside the playable zone to delete it
- [color=#ffff00]Right clicking[/color] the buttons cycles the object

How to play:
- Reach the end of the circuit as fast as possible
- [Up] to accelerate
- [Down] to brake
- [Left] and [Right] to turn

Hold [Up] to start
Use the arrow keys to move around.

To place the built conveyors inside the facility, put them on top of the pre-existing conveyors on the striped floor.

When a desired configuration of conveyors has been achieved, press [color=#ffff00]Enter[/color] to spawn a package on each one of the conveyors on the striped floor.

- Pressing [color=#FFFF00]Bksp[/color] at any point restarts the game.
- Use the [color=#ffff00]Mouse Scroll[/color] to rotate the camera.

Press [color=#FFFF00]Enter[/color] to start...
BLUEPRINTS TO THE ULTIMATE WAR MACHINE

Use the arrow keys to move around
and avoid the hazards.

The room behind the door has no energy, so you must plug 3 fuses in the generator to restore it. Since it is dark in there, you'll need to get a high-tech mask in the toolbox to proceed.

How to play:
[WASD] moves the character
[E] interacts with objects
[Mouse] looks around
[Space] toggles mask

1. Use the arrow keys to move around the maze.
2. Press "Z" to display the minimap.
3. Press "R" to restart the game.

1. Use the arrow keys to move around.
2. Press "Z" to jump.
3. Collide with the ghost to activate it.

[color=#ffff00]Mission Briefing:[/color] The reconnaissance team believes this antique edifice conceals a signal jammer that is crippling vital communications. Find and disable it.

[color=#ffff00]How to play:[/color]
- Click/Tap the objects to interact with them
- Some objects can be stored in the inventory
- Drag items out of the inventory to use them
- Drag an item on top of another to combine them
- Click/Tap outside a focused object to go back

[color=#ffff00]Click/Tap[/color] anywhere to start...
Use [color=#743932]\[Arrows][/color] to select level and [color=#743932]\[Space][/color] to start.
Use the arrow keys to move around and find the magic key.

How to play:

Land upright and very slowly on the illuminated site, then relaunch to repeat the process. A light on the rocket blinks green to indicate good landing conditions.

The arrows control the rocket.

Use the arrow keys to move around
and avoid the hazards.

In this example, you can enter a train and travel around the station. To start the train travel, enter it and press [color=#ffff00]\[Space][/color].

Controls:
- [color=#ffff00]\[WASD]:[/color] moves
- [color=#ffff00]\[Space]:[/color] activates the train
- [color=#ffff00]\[Mouse]:[/color] looks around

Press [color=#ffff00]\[Space][/color] to start...
Use the arrow keys to move the character or hold "Z" then press a single arrow key to move the entire platform instead.
Forge an Infinity Gemstone to win!

unique_values: This example is the 'HTML table' example, but uses HTML layers to allow a Sprite object to appear on top of the HTML table element. Look in the Layers Bar: layers which act as HTML layers are denoted by a special icon. That means HTML content can appear on top of that layer, and other layers above it appear on top of the HTML content. See the manual section on HTML layers for more details.
Learn more in the MDN guide Using AudioWorklet.
<!-- Loads content from project file htmlContent.html -->

Using JavaScript coding and HTML layers, you can insert a custom canvas in between HTML layers. In this case the Three.js library used to render a 3D model to a custom canvas in between HTML layers.
Credit: Three.js library — Model: Littlest Tokyo by Glen Fox, CC Attribution.

HTML element example

The content here is all shown inside a HTML Element object. This is a paragraph of text using the <p> tag. This example demonstrates several features of the HTML Element plugin, including:

  • HTML tags for styling like bold and italic
  • Formatting tags like headers, the details/summary tags, and this bullet point list
  • CSS styling (via the project file mystyles.css)
  • Using CSS animations to animate some elements
  • Including a button and detecting when it is clicked (via the element class)
